title: Yulia Svyrydenko - Wikipedia
snippet: Yulia Anatoliivna Svyrydenko (Ukrainian: Юлія Анатоліївна Свириденко, IPA: [ˈjul⁽ʲ⁾ijɐ ɐnɐˈtɔl⁽ʲ⁾ijiu̯nɐ swɪrɪˈdɛnko]; born 25 December 1985) is a Ukrainian politician who has served as the 19th prime minister of Ukraine since 17 July 2025.

title: PM's engagements with President Zelenskyy of Ukraine, President Macron of France, Chancellor Merz of Germany and European partners: 8 December 2025 - GOV.UK
snippet: The Prime Minister welcomed the President of Ukraine, Volodymyr Zelenskyy, the President of France, Emmanuel Macron, and the Chancellor of Germany, Friedrich Merz, to Downing Street today.

title: Leaders’ statement on Ukraine - Consilium
snippet: 15 December 2025 21:10 · This statement was adopted by President Costa, President von der Leyen, Prime Minister Frederiksen, President Stubb, President Macron, Chancellor Merz, Prime Minister Meloni, Prime Minister Schoof, Prime Minister Støre, Prime Minister Tusk, Prime Minister Kristersson, and Prime Minister Starmer. The Leaders welcomed significant progress on President Trump’s efforts to secure a just and lasting peace in Ukraine.
